OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FMs Langdale asked, "Did you think he
OL,7,Fcould end up killing someone?", to
OL,8,Fwhich Dr Seedat replied, "No, I
OL,9,Fdidn't."
OL,11,FHe told the inquiry, "When I said he
OL,12,Fwould kill someone, this would be
OL,13,Funintendedly.
OL,15,F"If he went and did the same thing
OL,16,Fagain and somebody jumped out of the
OL,17,Fwindow and maybe they were on a higher
OL,18,Ffloor, the consequences could be very
OL,19,Fdifferent.
OL,26,@nD@TOUoD@^O]pD@ZOUqD@HO]sD@VOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/57
