OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FThe witness, identified at the inquiry
OL,7,Fonly as Christopher, described the
OL,8,Fincident in Nottingham in 2022 as
OL,9,F"distressing" and said a police
OL,10,Fofficer was later "dismissive" and did
OL,11,Fnot arrest Calocane.
OL,13,FMobile phone footage of Calocane
OL,14,Fholding his flatmate in a headlock was
OL,15,Fshown to the inquiry as Christopher
OL,16,Fgave evidence.
OL,18,FChristopher said he believed he and
OL,19,Fothers were put at risk because they
OL,20,Fwere not given background information
OL,21,Fabout Calocane's medical history.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
