PN,37616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FHe was charged with assaulting an
OL,7,Femergency worker and was summoned to
OL,8,Fattend Nottingham Magistrates' Court
OL,9,Fin September 2022, but he failed to
OL,10,Fappear.
OL,12,FA warrant for his arrest was issued by
OL,13,Fthe court, but Calocane had not been
OL,14,Farrested by police before he committed
OL,15,Fthe attacks in June 2023.
OL,17,FThe Chief Constable of Nottinghamshire
OL,18,FPolice told the inquiry that Valdo
OL,19,FCalocane should have been arrested
OL,20,Fprior to the attacks.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G16/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FKate Meynell apologised and said there
OL,7,Fwere "no excuses" for why Calocane was
OL,8,Fnot arrested after he was charged with
OL,9,Fassaulting an emergency worker, but
OL,10,Ffailed to appear in court.
OL,12,FThe inquiry heard details of the
OL,13,Fwarrant were sent by Leicestershire
OL,14,FPolice to Nottinghamshire Police on
OL,15,FSeptember 23, 2022 by means of an
OL,16,F"occurrence" on the police's
OL,17,Finformation management system.
OL,26,@xD@AOUxD@LO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G17/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FThat went into an inbox on the system
OL,7,Fthe same day, but the inbox was not
OL,8,Fregularly checked, and there were no
OL,9,Frecorded updates on executing the
OL,10,Fwarrant before the day of the
OL,11,FNottingham attacks in June the
OL,12,Ffollowing year.
OL,14,FMrs Meynell made it clear that even if
OL,15,Fhe was arrested, it "would have been
OL,16,Fbailed from magistrates (had he been
OL,17,Farrested) and potentially it wouldn't
OL,18,Fhave been progressed with due to his
OL,19,Fmental health status at the time."
OL,26,@{D@bO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G18/57
