OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FDiscussing a policy relating to the
OL,7,Fway police deal with people with
OL,8,Fmental ill health, Ms Meynell admitted
OL,9,Fit had not been "understood on the
OL,10,Fground" by officers.
OL,12,FThe policy said a suspect having
OL,13,Fmental ill-health or learning
OL,14,Fdifficulties should not preclude a
OL,15,Ffull investigation, and there was a
OL,16,F"misconception" that arrest, interview
OL,17,Fand prosecution of persons with mental
OL,18,Fdisorder should not be considered due
OL,19,Fto mental capacity issues or the
OL,20,Fpublic interest.
OL,26,@qD@QOUrD@GO]xD@AOUxD@OO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G19/57
