OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37627
SC,0027
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FDr Tim Baker, a GP and partner at the
OL,7,FUniversity of Nottingham's Cripps
OL,8,FHealth Centre, where Calocane was a
OL,9,Fpatient from September 2017, said he
OL,10,Fwould expect a patient to be
OL,11,Fdischarged from secondary care "only
OL,12,Fwhen and if it was considered safe to
OL,13,Fdo so" and that discharges from
OL,14,Fsecondary care are "specialist
OL,15,Fdecisions based on careful review of
OL,16,Fdiagnosis, risk and safety".
OL,26,@sD@`OUuD@FO]vD@TOUxD@[O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G27/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
