OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37629
SC,0029
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FBefore the inquiry, a report revealed
OL,7,Fhe'd was not forced to have long-
OL,8,Flasting antipsychotic medication
OL,9,Fbecause he did not like needles.
OL,11,FA mental health nurse told the inquiry
OL,12,FCalocane "lied, deceived and
OL,13,Foutmanoeuvred" medical staff.
OL,15,FGary Carter, who was part of the Early
OL,16,FIntervention in Psychosis (EIP) team
OL,17,Fand was Calocane's care co-ordinator
OL,18,Fbetween April and September 2022, said
OL,19,F"95%" of what he knows about the
OL,20,FNottingham killer he has learned since
OL,21,Fthe fatal attacks in June 2023.
OL,26,@tD@JOUuD@NO]{D@AOU{D@EO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G29/57
