OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FOne of the most serious claims made by
OL,7,Fthe families during the inquiry
OL,8,Fconcerned an alleged "cover-up" by the
OL,9,FCrown Prosecution Service, the body
OL,10,Fresponsible for conducting criminal
OL,11,Fprosecutions in England and Wales.
OL,13,FAfter Calocane was sentenced in
OL,14,FJanuary 2024, the CPS said medical
OL,15,Fexperts said his condition "impaired
OL,16,Fhis ability to exercise self-control".
OL,18,FAlan Murphy is a CPS specialist
OL,19,Fprosecutor and told the inquiry it was
OL,20,Fclear mental health issues would play
OL,21,Fa part in the case early on.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G40/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
