PN,37641
SC,0041
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FOn 23 November 2023, the inquiry heard
OL,7,Fthat a meeting had been held for
OL,8,Fprosecutors to decide whether to
OL,9,Faccept Calocane's guilty pleas to
OL,10,Fmanslaughter on the grounds of
OL,11,Fdiminished responsibility.
OL,13,FThe inquiry heard a number of experts
OL,14,Fhad been instructed by the CPS to
OL,15,Fassess Calocane and his defence had
OL,16,Falso produced its own psychiatric
OL,17,Freport. However, the victims' families
OL,18,Fhad raised concerns about those
OL,19,Freports.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G41/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37642
SC,0042
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FMr Murphy defended the process,
OL,7,Fsaying, "We had a very thorough - in
OL,8,Fmy view - report from (forensic
OL,9,Fpsychiatrist Prof Nigel Blackwood) and
OL,10,Fwe were going to get a further report
OL,11,Ffrom (a second forensic psychologist
OL,12,FDr Richard Latham), so if we needed
OL,13,Fmore time we would've asked for it,
OL,14,Fbut we didn't need it."
OL,16,FCalocane was sentenced for
OL,17,Fmanslaughter and attempted murder in
OL,18,FJanuary 2024, after the Crown
OL,19,FProsecution Service (CPS) accepted his
OL,20,Fnot guilty pleas to murder on the
OL,21,Fgrounds of diminished responsibility.
OL,26,@pD@WpmqD@bpnsD@FpmtD@Rpn
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G42/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
