OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FSharon Miller described the injuries
OL,7,Fshe received to the inquiry, "I broke
OL,8,Fmy toe, five ribs, I lacerated my
OL,9,Fspleen, and I've got a big hole in the
OL,10,Fback of my leg that got badly
OL,11,Finfected".
OL,13,FAsked if she felt "sidelined" as a
OL,14,Fvictim who survived, Ms Miller said,
OL,15,F"Definitely."
OL,17,FShe added, "I felt like I had come out
OL,18,Fof hospital and was pushed aside."
OL,26,@uD@SOUuD@]O]wD@AOUwD@MO]yD@LOUzD@bO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G49/57
