OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FAll eyes were on the inquiry when the
OL,7,FCalocane family took the stand.
OL,8,FCeleste and Elias Calocane were both
OL,9,Fforced to explain whether they could
OL,10,Fknow the level of violence Valdo was
OL,11,Fcapable of.
OL,13,FThe mother of triple killer Valdo
OL,14,FCalocane told police she could not
OL,15,Fbelieve her son was a "delinquent"
OL,16,Fwhen he was first arrested, years
OL,17,Fbefore the Nottingham Attacks.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G51/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37652
SC,0052
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FCeleste Calocane told a public inquiry
OL,7,Fshe wanted her son to be treated in
OL,8,Fhospital for his mental health as
OL,9,Fearly as May 2020.
OL,11,FBoth Mrs Calocane and her son said
OL,12,Fthat they weren't listened to by the
OL,13,Fhealth service, "This system is so
OL,14,Fbroken... no one listened to you.
OL,15,FBefore you get to crisis you need to
OL,16,Fbe doing prevention. Before you get to
OL,17,Fcrisis, crisis is too late."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G52/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
