PN,37653
SC,0053
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,FMrs Calocane, who gave birth to her
OL,7,Feldest son, Valdo, at the age of 16,
OL,8,Fspoke about his first arrest in May
OL,9,F2020 for causing damage to a
OL,10,Fneighbour's door.
OL,12,FShe said, "When they called to say
OL,13,F'your son's been arrested for
OL,14,Fburglary'... I said 'he's 28 years
OL,15,Fold, how can he be arrested for
OL,16,Fburglary? He's never done anything
OL,17,Flike that. That's out of character. I
OL,18,Fcan't accept that.'
OL,26,@tD@KOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G53/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37654
SC,0054
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1781021473
OL,3,CCould Calocane have been stopped? Key
OL,4,Cmoments from the Nottingham Inquiry
OL,6,F"I said, 'You're telling me he's
OL,7,Fbecoming a delinquent. That's not my
OL,8,Fson.'"
OL,10,FValdo Calocane sent his brother
OL,11,Fmessages about hurting "permanently",
OL,12,Fbut his brother said he thought he was
OL,13,Ftalking about killing himself.
OL,15,FCalocane also told his brother Elias
OL,16,Fhe was "thinking about red rum", which
OL,17,Fis murder spelt backwards.
OL,19,FBut Elias told the Nottingham Attacks
OL,20,FInquiry his brother was a "calm and
OL,21,Fpeaceful" person.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@FO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G54/57
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
